title: Grateful Dead Live at Salt Palace on 1981-08-12
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Friend Of The Devil, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Jack A Roe-> CC Rider, Althea, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance

Set 2

Might As Well-> Women Are Smarter, Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Spanish Jam-> Truckin'-> Morning Dew-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Thanks We needed this copy up here for years. listening to the Dew now. My personal favorite song as far as ballads go that is. Sound is very good on this song. Have not checked out much of rest yet. Can surely hear everything though. Jerry's voice is crisp
- Very nice jams, and nice work on the redux.
Solid Show Highlights: Althea, Saint Of Circumstance, Drums, Morning Dew

Favorite Scarlet>Fire Love this Scarlet>Fire. It was this version that turned me into a Deadhead as a freshman in college in 1985. Listening to this gave me a glimpse into the world of improvisation and music with no boundaries. I will always love it and no matter how many times I hear it, I will never tire of it. Also just as a matter of record... the dead played Spanish Jam just 3 months before this show at Nassau, so the break out of Might as Well was a bigger deal.
wrong Encore was at that show and the Encore was a amazing Baby Blue.  i dont know why you even tried to finish it off with that
